Google Remotely Disables Malicious Smartphone Software, FT Says

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-08T05:30:54Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-08/google-remotely-disables-malicious-smartphone-software-ft-says.html
  Google Inc. (GOOG)  is remotely disabling
malicious software voluntarily installed by more than 250,000
owners of Android smartphones, the first time the company has
taken such action to removed dangerous applications, the
Financial Times reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
